args:
The Leaders of the Twelve Wyrmclans of Hinomoto:
Though united in their aim to govern their land,
divided are their ambitions, each a worthy
rival vying for the gloried seat of shogun.

Two such clan leaders, having just returned from
a journey to spread good fortune among other
nations, now answer a summons to the
homestead of Ieyasu; leader of the Boar Clan.
The Eastern Island Nation of Hinomoto\nEstate of Ieyasu; Leader of the Boar Clan
An express invitation of this nature begets\nbusiness most vital, I must imagine?
Nobunaga; Leader of the Horse Clan
Indeed. I would not have bade you\nvisit otherwise.
Ieyasu; Leader of the Boar Clan
What's your angle here, gathering three\nWyrmclan leaders under one roof?
Mitsuhide; Leader of the Mouse Clan
We gonna get a head start on this whole\nfight for succession, maybe?
...Ah, thank you, this tea is exquisite.\nWait...are we just here for tea?!
I thought a discussion over tea most fitting\nfor what I'd like to address today.
Pray tell me, fellow clan leaders:\nWhat qualities define an apt ruler?
A fascinating question indeed—and\none I would be delighted to answer!
By all means, Nobunaga.\nThe floor is yours.
It's simple, really. What a ruler needs...\nis the strength to guide her people!

To inspire hopes and dreams in the people,
and walk forward together with them.
For a nation cannot prosper unless
its people grow.
And you, Ieyasu? Since you raised the\nquestion, you ought to answer as well.
Very well. What I deem necessary for a\nleader...is unwavering righteousness.
Without justice and honor in your heart,\nyou risk treading down the wrong path.
Might you be trying to suggest that I am\na fool of a ruler who races forth recklessly?
Perish the thought. It is no more than a\ndifference in where our priorities lie.
*sigh* Yeah, yeah, you're both admirable.\nEveryone is sooo very surprised.
Do not be so insipid, Mitsuhide. You are\na clan leader as well, are you not?
I would hear your opinion as well.\nYour perspective is valued here.
＂What makes an apt ruler,＂ huh? Well...

If you're too stiff you'll eventually snap.
That's why you've gotta chill out every
once in a while. ...Or ALL the while.
Especially if you're ruling over folks.

So if you follow that thinking to its logical
conclusion, a laid-back ruler makes for a
laid-back domain. Peace and tranquility
and all that, y'know?
Er, well, I suppose I can follow the thread\nof your logic...
Don't be fooled, Ieyasu. She's only trying\nto justify her own behavior.
You wound me. I'm just giving you my\nopinion here.
Besides, becoming shogun is the last thing\non my mind. I've got a good thing going\nright now, and I'm not about to mess it up.
No fooling. Being responsible for\nall of Hinomoto really ain't my style.
If I somehow ended up with the job...I'd\nconsider it. But we've already got qualified\nfolks out there like you itching to handle it.
Chilling out in my own domain sounds\na lot more my speed.
I suppose it does. Have you no aspirations\nwhatsoever, though?
The only thing I aspire to do is kick back,\nrelax, and enjoy this ride we call life.
...Incidentally, I think it's about time you\ntell us what you're really getting at here,\nIeyasu.
You wanna ask us about something else,\nright? About, oh, I dunno...\nThe Alberian prince, maybe?
I'm afraid you'll have to elaborate.
We had just gotten back from our journey\nto spread fortune when you first invited\nus here.
Then you launched into asking us what\nwe think is necessary for a person to be\na good ruler.
You know who else is a ruler?\nThe prince of Alberia.
Basically, you were hoping our chat would\nshed some light on the current state of\nAlberia. Am I right, or am I right?
...You're as sharp as ever. It was pointless\nto employ smoke and mirrors with you.
Why did you not state your intent from the\nvery beginning, Ieyasu?

You were concerned about how it would
look, right? A Wyrmclan leader backing a
foreign nation... It'd be pretty easy to use
that as a smear tactic against you.
Aha ha. It's nothing so grave. You might\nsay I was simply...＂covering my bases,＂\nas I believe the saying goes.
You're a wily one, Ieyasu. Still, can't say\nI'm complaining about sharing travel\nstories over a nice cup of tea.
Alberia was a pretty lively place.\nLots'a real characters there. That said...
There's something about that prince that's\nbugging me.
What, really? You showed no signs\nof discontent.
Well, it didn't have anything to do with\nthe fortune-spreading, y'know? It's just a,\nI don't know...a personal interest.
I can't help wondering what might happen\nif I meddle a bit.

In any case, my curiosity's gotten the
better of me, so on that note... I'm headed
off to Alberia. You guys have fun with
everything here.
Yep. Make up a good excuse for me if\nChitose comes calling, Nobunaga. Byeee!
Hey! Wait, you can't just—*sigh* Aaand\nshe's off on yet another flight of fancy.
She's been different ever since she\nbecame a Wyrmclan leader.
Indeed. Honestly, that Mitsuhide... What\ncould she possibly want to do in Alberia?
Now, let's see...\nHow shall I conquer this castle?
